WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.960
That, perhaps, is the real trick of these

00:00:02.960 --> 00:00:03.520
little pictures.

00:00:04.260 --> 00:00:06.040
The very same book could sit on a

00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:08.360
bishop's shelf as a devout meditation and

00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:11.060
circulate among reformers as a joke at the

00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:11.780
bishop's expense.

00:00:12.360 --> 00:00:15.280
The piety is the disguise; the protest is

00:00:15.280 --> 00:00:18.020
the payload — and both are completely true

00:00:18.020 --> 00:00:18.600
at once.

00:00:19.240 --> 00:00:20.780
Holbein understood that the most

00:00:20.780 --> 00:00:22.960
unsettling thing you can show the powerful

00:00:22.960 --> 00:00:24.480
is not that they will die.

00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:25.620
They knew that.

00:00:25.880 --> 00:00:27.520
It's that when they die, they will be

00:00:27.520 --> 00:00:30.100
exactly equal to the peasant in the field

00:00:30.100 --> 00:00:32.260
— and that the peasant, of the two,

00:00:32.260 --> 00:00:34.600
may be the one who finally gets to

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:34.920
rest.
